{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Hello!\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Hello! I'm Sculptor, an AI coding agent made by Imbue. I'm here to help you write code, fix bugs, and answer questions about your codebase.\\n\\nI can see you're working in a git repository on the branch `branch_1`. How can I help you today?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": \"Run this command: fallocate -l 100000000 big_file.img\", \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"I'll run that command to create a 100MB file using fallocate.\", \"type\": \"text\"}, {\"id\": \"toolu_01Gx6ENDE8y85tFH1GEhX6pi\", \"input\": {\"command\": \"fallocate -l 100000000 big_file.img\", \"description\": \"Create 100MB file using fallocate\"}, \"name\": \"Bash\", \"type\": \"tool_use\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_01GWKpFNdHk9WUmJTkaw4487", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Done! I've created a 100MB file named `big_file.img` in your current directory using fallocate. This command quickly allocates disk space without actually writing data to it, making it much faster than other methods for creating large files.\n\nNote: Since this is a binary file that's not typically tracked in git, you may want to add `*.img` to your `.gitignore` file to prevent it from being committed. Would you like me to do that?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 7, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 4176, "cache_read_input_tokens": 11124, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 4176, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 105, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": \"Please write a 5-10 word title for the following conversation:\\n\\nUser: Warmup\\n\\nClaude: I'll help you warm up by exploring the codebase structure. Let me get an overview of what we're working with.\\n\\n```bash\\nfind /code -type f -name \\\"*.py\\\" -o -name \\\"*.txt\\\" -o -name \\\"*.md\\\" -o -name \\\"*.json\\\" | head -20\\n```\\n\\n```\\n/code/.git/objects/pack/pack-08396dbe4b29f9b6e3bb5b97fdacbc4f6b44e7d3.pack\\n/code/.git/objects/pack/pack-08396dbe4b29f9b6e3bb5b97fdacbc4f6b44e7d3.idx\\n/code/.git/refs/heads/branch_1\\n/code/.git/config\\n/code/.git/HEAD\\n/code/app.py\\n/code/data.txt\\n/code/README.md\\n```\\n\\nLet me get a better view of the directory structure:\\n\\n```bash\\nls -la /code\\n```\\n\\n```\\ntotal 36\\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Sep 16 10:51 .\\ndrwxr-xr-x 1 root root 4096 Oct 22 13:40 ..\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  224 Sep 16 10:51 README.md\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root   89 Sep 16 10:51 app.py\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root   69 Sep 16 10:51 data.txt\\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 4096 Sep 16 10:51 .git\\n```\\n\\nNow let me examine the main files:\\n\\n```bash\\ncat /code/app.py\\n```\\n\\n```\\n# This is a simple app\\nprint(\\\"Hello, World!\\\")\\n\\n# Some comment\\nx = 10\\n```\\n\\n```bash\\ncat /code/data.txt\\n```\\n\\n```\\nname: John\\nage: 30\\ncity: New York\\n```\\n\\n```bash\\ncat /code/README.md\\n```\\n\\n```\\n# My Project\\n\\nThis is a simple project with:\\n- app.py: Main application\\n- data.txt: Data file\\n```\\n\\nGreat! Here's what I found in the codebase:\\n\\n**Project Structure:**\\n- /code/app.py - Main application file (89 bytes)\\n- /code/data.txt - Data file with name, age, city information (69 bytes)\\n- /code/README.md - Project documentation (224 bytes)\\n\\n**File Contents:**\\n\\n1. **/code/app.py** - Simple Python application that prints \\\"Hello, World!\\\" and sets a variable\\n2. **/code/data.txt** - Contains structured data with name (John), age (30), and city (New York)\\n3. **/code/README.md** - Basic documentation describing the project files\\n\\nThe repository is on **branch_1** with recent commits including \\\"Stuff\\\", \\\"app.py commit\\\", \\\"add some cool data\\\", and an initial commit.\\n\\nI'm ready to help you search for specific files or content in this codebase. What would you like to explore?\\n\\nRespond with the title for the conversation and nothing else.\", \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 0.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", "id": "msg_01M8FZR8PCcTqJAVk8SA4dvg", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Codebase Exploration and Project Structure Overview"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 823, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 13, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Hello!\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Hello! I'm Sculptor, an AI coding agent made by Imbue. I'm here to help you write code, fix bugs, and answer questions about your codebase.\\n\\nI can see you're working in a git repository on the branch `branch_1`. How can I help you today?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Run this command: fallocate -l 100000000 big_file.img\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"I'll run that command to create a 100MB file using fallocate.\", \"type\": \"text\"}, {\"id\": \"toolu_01Gx6ENDE8y85tFH1GEhX6pi\", \"input\": {\"command\": \"fallocate -l 100000000 big_file.img\", \"description\": \"Create 100MB file using fallocate\"}, \"name\": \"Bash\", \"type\": \"tool_use\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Done! I've created a 100MB file named `big_file.img` in your current directory using fallocate. This command quickly allocates disk space without actually writing data to it, making it much faster than other methods for creating large files.\\n\\nNote: Since this is a binary file that's not typically tracked in git, you may want to add `*.img` to your `.gitignore` file to prevent it from being committed. Would you like me to do that?\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Hello\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_018Pz7fuudjPCAy2FYfwPvZb", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hello again! Is there anything you'd like me to help you with in your codebase?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 3778, "cache_read